<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Barcelona have confirmed the sale of Arturo Vidal to Inter Milan but the club will receive just £917,000 for the midfielder.</p>

<p>Inter were keen to sign the Chile international in January after Vidal became embroiled in a contract dispute with Barcelona.</p>

<p>The Catalans accused Vidal of trying to force through a move to Inter by opening a lawsuit against the club for alleged unpaid bonuses.</p>

<p>Vidal waves goodbye to Barca after winning La Liga and the Spanish Super Cup at Camp Nou</p>

<p>Vidal spent two seasons at Barca, scoring 11 goals and making 10 assists in 96 appearances</p>

<p>Vidal has now got his wish after the two clubs came to an agreement, which both clubs confirmed on Tuesday.  </p>

<p>A statement on Barca's website read: 'Barcelona and Inter Milan have reached an agreement for the transfer of the player Arturo Vidal. The Italian club will pay FC Barcelona 1 million euros in variables.</p>

<p>'FC Barcelona would like to publicly express their gratitude to Arturo Vidal for his commitment and dedication and wishes him all the best for the future.'</p>

<p>Vidal joins Chile team-mate Alexis Sanchez at Inter and becomes sixth Chilean to play for club</p>

<p>Vidal scored 11 goals in 96 appearances his two seasons at the club, which saw him win La Liga in 2018/19.</p>

<p>That success saw him win an eight consecutive league title in three different countries, while he also added the Spanish Super Cup to his collection.</p>

<p>Vidal also scored the final goal in a 5-1 thrashing of Real Madrid at the Nou Camp and will now hope to add to his glittering trophy cabinet at San Siro. </p>

<p>In joining the club, he becomes the sixth Chilean to play for Inter, following Ivan Zamorano, David Pizarro, Gary Medel, Luis Jimenez and Alexis Sanchez.</p>
